OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1775146264
OL,3,CSeasonal work permit policy to be
OL,4,Creviewed by politicians
OL,6,FThe Employer Pays Principle sets out
OL,7,Fthat recruitment fees and related
OL,8,Fcosts should not be taken from the
OL,9,Fworkers themselves, either directly or
OL,10,Findirectly, but instead paid by the
OL,11,Fperson contracting them.
OL,13,FDeputy Poree writes that recruitment
OL,14,Ffees "are used to retain workers in
OL,15,F'debt bondage'" and calls this "one of
OL,16,Fthe factors of financial control
OL,17,Fidentified in modern slavery".
OL,26,@uD@Krr
